value: Breeds on the tundras, mountains and plateaus of Europe and Asia from Scotland, Scandinavia, northern Russia (including Novaya Zemlya) and northern Siberia, south to Germany, the Tirol, the Urals, Ala-tau, Altai, Sayan Mountains and probably to the mountains of Transbaikalia. Winters in the lands bordering the Mediterranean; Arabia and Persia.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: Palearctic winter visitor, stony steppe, semi-desert, marginal cultivation: all across North Africa and to N Sudan in Red Sea area.
Stony steppes, plains, newly plowed fields and marginal grassland (breeding); open stony or sandy areas, less frequently marshes, mudflats, and seacoasts (nonbreeding).
stony steppe, plains, grassland, ploughed fields, coasts, marsh
